This module allow use blocks like in Django.

In your layout template define blocks:

<html>
<head>
	<title><?php $self->block('title'); ?>Layout title<?php $self->endblock('title') ?></title>
</head>
<body>
	<?php $self->block('content') ?>
		Layout content
	<?php $self->endblock('content') ?>
</body>
</html>

And add in child view this:

<?php 
	$self->extend('layout');
?>
<?php $self->block('content') ?>
	Child content 
<?php $self->endblock('content') ?>

Now you can simple call child view:

$this->request->response = View::factory('child');

Blocks can be nested:

<?php $self->block('content') ?>

	<p>Content</p>
	
	<?php $self->block('left') ?>
		<p>Left</p>
	<?php $self->endblock('left') ?>
	
	<?php $self->block('right') ?>
		<p>Right</p>
	<?php $self->endblock('right') ?>
	
<?php $self->endblock('content') ?>